parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt becomes stuck
the seat belt cable comes out of the track
the seat belt stops working completely
the seat belt loosens while driving
the seat belt will not return to the locked position
the seat belt makes a clicking noise
the seat belt is covered in grease
the motor in the seat belt burns out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt recall repairs can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt continues to malfunction after recall repairs
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt becomes stuck
the seat belt cable comes out of the track
the seat belt stops working completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips
transmission fails to engage
transmission jumps gears
vehicle shuts off while driving
vehicle hesitates or jerks forward
engine high idles
transmission grabs and jerks the vehicle forward
squealing rear tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle and viscous clutch failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Wheels lock up
feeling of brakes being on when they are not
inability to move forward or backward
noise as if something snapped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shift linkage failure can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting into gear
need to depress button on stick shift to shift into gear
vehicle goes into neutral when shifting into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents and stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls and dies without warning
the engine check light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to catastrophic damage and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power.
symptoms: The radiator overheats and bursts
the fan belt shorts out
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially stall, increasing the risk of accidents and stranding the driver.
symptoms: Oil leaks
head gasket failure
oil drain plug failure
main seal valve failure
oil burning inside the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft pulley can cause catastrophic damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs and potentially stranding the driver.
symptoms: The bolt that holds the pulley to the crank falls off
causing valves to crash and catastrophic damage to the engine
the pulley breaks off while driving.
